---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy · Blu Baby Show" description="How Blu Baby Show handles your information.">
  <section class="section legal">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Blu Baby Show</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="muted">Last updated: July 2026</p>

      <p>We keep this simple, because you're a busy parent.</p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <p>If you join our newsletter, we collect your <strong>email address</strong> — nothing else. If you
        ever buy something, our payment partner handles your payment details; we never see or store your card.</p>

      <h2>How we use it</h2>
      <p>Your email is used only to send you our weekly note and occasional updates about Blu. We never sell,
        rent, or share your email with anyone. You can unsubscribe any time with one tap.</p>

      <h2>Children's information</h2>
      <p>Blu Baby Show is a brand made <em>for parents</em>. We do not knowingly collect personal information
        from children. Any product that involves uploading a photo of your child is used <strong>only</strong>
        to create your order, is processed with your consent, and is not stored or used for anything else.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions? Email <a href="mailto:hello@blubabyshow.com">hello@blubabyshow.com</a>.</p>

      <p class="muted"><small>This is a plain-language summary. A full policy will be published before any
        paid or photo-based product launches.</small></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .legal { padding-top: calc(var(--nav-h) + 2rem); max-width: 720px; }
  .legal h1 { margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .legal h2 { font-size: 1.3rem; margin-top: 2rem; color: var(--blu-deep); }
  .legal a { color: var(--blu-d); text-decoration: underline; }
</style>
